Jako zbiór danych został wybrany popularny "cifar10". Został ona stworzony raczej do nauki problemu klasyfikacji, ponieważ zawiera ona obrazki z przypisanymi klasami. W tym projekcie zostały użyte tylko obrazki-X. Na wejściu były one zamieniane na czarno-białe.

(y_train, _), (y_test, _) = cifar10.load_data()
y_train = y_train.astype('float32') / 255
y_test = y_test.astype('float32') / 255
x_train = np.expand_dims([cv.cvtColor(x, cv.COLOR_RGB2GRAY) for x in y_train], axis=3)
x_test = np.expand_dims([cv.cvtColor(x, cv.COLOR_RGB2GRAY) for x in y_test], axis=3)
print(y_train.shape)

class Encoder(Model):
  def __init__(self, filters: list, kernel_size: int, batch_momentum: float = None, dropout_rate: float = None):
    super(Encoder, self).__init__(name='Encoder')

    self.my_layers = []
    for i, filter in enumerate(filters):
      # stride = (i%2)+1 ## 1 in even, 2 in odd, to avoid pooling
      stride = 2
      self.my_layers.append(
          Conv2D(filters=filter, kernel_size=kernel_size, strides=stride, padding='same', activation="relu")
      )
      if batch_momentum: self.my_layers.append(BatchNormalization(momentum=batch_momentum))
      if dropout_rate: self.my_layers.append(Dropout(dropout_rate))
  
  def call(self, x):
    for layer in self.my_layers:
      x = layer(x)
    return x

class Decoder(Model):
  def __init__(self, filters, kernel, batch_momentum: float = None, dropout_rate: float = None):
    super(Decoder, self).__init__(name='Decoder')
    
    self.myLayers = []

    for filter in filters:
      self.myLayers.append(Conv2DTranspose(filters=filter,kernel_size=kernel,padding = "same",activation='relu',strides=2))
      if batch_momentum: self.myLayers.append(BatchNormalization(momentum = batch_momentum))
      if dropout_rate: self.myLayers.append(Dropout(dropout_rate))
      
    self.myLayers.append(Conv2D(3,kernel,padding = "same",activation='sigmoid',strides=1))

  def call(self, x):
    for layer in self.myLayers:
      x = layer(x)
    return x  

class Autoencoder(Model):
  def __init__(self, filters, kernel=3, dropout_rate=None, batch_momentum=None):
    super(Autoencoder, self).__init__(name="Autoencoder")
    self.encoder = Encoder(filters, kernel, batch_momentum, dropout_rate)
    self.decoder = Decoder(filters[::-1], kernel, batch_momentum, dropout_rate)

  def call(self, x):
    x = self.encoder(x)
    x = self.decoder(x)
    return x

filters = [64, 128, 256]
dropout_rate = [0.1,0.3,0.5,0.7,0.9]
models = []

for dr in dropout_rate:
    optimizer = Adam(learning_rate=0.001)

    model = Autoencoder(filters=filters, kernel=3, dropout_rate=dr)

    model.compile(optimizer=optimizer, loss='mse', metrics=['accuracy'])

    model.myhistory = model.fit(x_train, y_train, epochs=5, batch_size=128)

    models.append(model)

def draw_plots(models, titles, name_of_list, list):
  fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(ncols=2, figsize=(20,10))

  ax1.set_ylabel("loss")
  ax1.set_xlabel('epoch')
  ax2.set_ylabel("accuracy")
  ax2.set_xlabel('epoch')

  for i, model in enumerate(models):
      ax1.plot(model.myhistory.history["loss"], label = f"model{i} {name_of_list}{list[i]}")
      ax2.plot(model.myhistory.history["accuracy"], label = f"model{i} {name_of_list}{list[i]}")

  ax1.legend()
  ax2.legend()
  ax1.set_title(f"{titles} - loss")
  ax2.set_title(f"{titles} - accuracy")
draw_plots(models, "DropoutTest", "dropout_rate=", [0.1,0.3,0.5,0.7,0.9])

def draw_pic(model, path_to_pic, title): 
  y = cv.cvtColor(cv.imread(path_to_pic), cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB).astype('float32') / 255
  x = cv.cvtColor(y, cv.COLOR_RGB2GRAY)
  Y = model.predict(x.reshape(1, x.shape[0], x.shape[1], 1))[0]

  fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3) = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(9, 4.5), tight_layout=True)

  ax1.imshow(x.reshape(x.shape[0], x.shape[1]), cmap='gray')
  ax2.imshow(Y)
  ax3.imshow(y)

  ax2.set_title(title)

  ax1.set_xlabel('input')
  ax2.set_xlabel('output')
  ax3.set_xlabel('expected')

draw_pic(models[0], "See.jpeg", "Dropout test result")
